    Multisets.Multiset — Type.

    A Multiset is an unordered collection of things with repetition permitted. A new Multiset container is created with Multiset{T}() where T is the type of the objects held in the multiset. If T is omitted, it defaults to Any.

    A Multiset can be created from a collection list (such as a Vector or Set) with Multiset(list). If an element is repeated in list it has the appropriate multiplicity.

    Multisets.set_braces_show — Function.

    Set braces display mode for multisets, like this:

    {1,2,2,3,3,3,3}

    See also set_short_show and set_julia_show.

    Multisets.set_julia_show — Function.

    Set Julia style display mode for multisets, like this:

    Multiset(Int64[1,2,2,3,3,3,3])

    See also set_short_show and set_braces_show.

    Multisets.set_short_show — Function.

    Set show display mode for multisets, like this:

    Multiset{Int64} with 7 elements

    See also set_braces_show and set_julia_show.
